  h1 SEIZE AND SCOOP
  p When a koala population is under threat from mining or a development, translocation is often proposed by industry. This involves moving koalas to alternative habitat that is already under protection, instead of protecting their existing habitat.
  p This method of management has been proposed to deal with the koala population in the Gunnedah region, who live at the newly approved Shenhua Watermark mine site.
  
